<DOC><DOCNO> AP900723-0077 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-23-90 1311EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--WeaponsTheft     07-23 0163</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Weapons Theft,0168</SECOND><HEAD>Police Storm Apartment, Recover Weapons from Finn</HEAD><DATELINE>OSLO, Norway (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Anti-terrorist police shot tear gas and thenstormed an apartment to arrest a Finn who stole machine guns andother weapons from a private collection, news reports said Monday.   Newspapers said police surrounded the building where the38-year-old Finn lived, but the suspect, who has not been named,refused to surrender.   After 90 minutes, police fired tear gas through his apartmentwindows, broke down his door and arrested him without firing anyshots.   The man was released Sunday after he reportedly confessing tothe theft.   Police said after the raid they recovered 57 of the 117 weaponsstolen from a private Norwegian collection on June 26.   Police said some of the weapons were found in the man'sapartment while additional weapons were hidden at a barn where thesuspect took police. The cache included seven machine guns,pistols, ammunition and other weapons.   They were apparently stolen for profit.</TEXT></DOC>